</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: DJango; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"DJango">{
  "data": {
    "sampleResources": [
      {
        "id": 25,
        "name": "a resource",
        "customerRating": "evil"
      },
      {
        "id": 37,
        "name": "your resource",
        "customerRating": "bad"
      }
    ]
  },
  "paging": {
    "count": 13,
    "pageSize": 2,
    "nextPageKey": "37"
  }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"DesigningtheSwaggerDefinitionObjects-Fieldandparameternaming">Fie=
ld and parameter naming</h2>
<ul>
<li>Declare commonly used fields using their standard names. For example, c=
urrencyCode.</li>
<li>Use concise, consistent, unambiguous, non-abbreviated, (lower) camel ca=
se for all field names in JSON.&nbsp; For example, to define the field 'fir=
st name' declare it as 'firstName'</li>
<li>In some cases, acronyms are acceptable but must be capitalised. i.e. "T=
FN" and "ABN" are acceptable if and only if the acronyms are commonly used =
within the domain, at a business level, not a technical or system level.</l=
i>
<li>Name fields using business terminology with guidance from the available=
 domain models, ECDM, IFW (aka GESB) or industry standards. fields are not =
based on provider interface names.</li>
<li>Make the field names meaningful and easily understood without requiring=
 a separate description.</li>
<li>Provide a concise, unambiguous and succinct description. Don't simply s=
et the description to the field name.</li>
<li>Design the interface with the consumer (or&nbsp;consumers) where possib=
le. The API requests and responses should be driven&nbsp;from the&nbsp;cons=
umer use case - not enterprise and application data&nbsp;models.</li>
</ul><br>
<h2 id=3D"DesigningtheSwaggerDefinitionObjects-Enumerations">Enumerations</=
h2>
<p>Enumerations should expose concise domain business values.. Internal tra=
nslations must be done by configuration.</p>
<p>Enumerations should not be used for any property that exposes enterprise=
 reference data (ERD). Instead the property should expose a string field an=
d the swagger description needs to document the ERD Classification (aka Cat=
egory)</p>
<h2 id=3D"DesigningtheSwaggerDefinitionObjects-EnterpriseReferenceData">Ent=
erprise Reference Data</h2>
<p>Some fields can expose enterprise reference data (ERD), either for the r=
equest or response. For fields or parameters that are reference data, the s=
wagger should clearly call out that the field exposes ERD and the classific=
ation used.&nbsp; "The product repayment type qualifies if the mortgage arr=
angement is based on Principal and Interest or Interest Only . This is a en=
terprise reference data field based on the 'FinancialServiceRepaymentType' =
classification scheme."</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
